{"sha": "0ebaea3b6677ef8edfa5638800304db1a4f7c2f8", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0MTM2NTMxMDA6MGViYWVhM2I2Njc3ZWY4ZWRmYTU2Mzg4MDAzMDRkYjFhNGY3YzJmOA==", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Paul Scharnofske", "email": "asynts@gmail.com", "date": "2020-11-11T09:29:37Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Jonathan Wakely", "email": "jwakely@redhat.com", "date": "2020-11-11T11:13:31Z"}, "message": "libstdc++: Assigning to a joinable std::jthread calls std::terminate\n\nMove assigning to a std::jthread that represents a thread of execution\nneeds to send a stop request and join that running thread. Otherwise the\nstd::thread data member will terminate in its assignment operator.\n\nCo-authored-by: Jonathan Wakely <jwakely@redhat.com>\n\nlibstdc++-v3/ChangeLog:\n\n\t* include/std/thread (jthread::operator=(jthread&&)): Transfer\n\tany existing state to a temporary that will request a stop and\n\tthen join.\n\t* testsuite/30_threads/jthread/jthread.cc: Test move assignment.", "tree": {"sha": "76e8e5d3415c5a0039034cd4f5ad249032996a4a", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/76e8e5d3415c5a0039034cd4f5ad249032996a4a"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/0ebaea3b6677ef8edfa5638800304db1a4f7c2f8", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/0ebaea3b6677ef8edfa5638800304db1a4f7c2f8", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/0ebaea3b6677ef8edfa5638800304db1a4f7c2f8", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/0ebaea3b6677ef8edfa5638800304db1a4f7c2f8/comments", "author": {"login": "asynts", "id": 31994781, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMxOTk0Nzgx", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/31994781?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/asynts", "html_url": "https://github.com/asynts", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/asynts/followers", "foll